Configure Placeholder Settings
----field----
field: {00E1D306-96BD-4B32-85B4-CD63C53CC6C1}
name: Abstract
key: abstract
content-length: 141

<p>Learn how to limit which controls and sublayouts can go where on a site. Presented in the context of the Build My First Site exercise.</p>
----field----
field: {5A5684BB-8B54-44F6-ABCC-2BADA05ADA5D}
name: Body
key: body
content-length: 1159

<h3>Discussion</h3>
<p>In the previous section we learned how to bind our presentation elements and data items. The previous method is useful when you know in advance which Sublayouts and Renderings you wish to use in advance. However, often you want to give end users some choice in selecting Sublayouts to display onto a page. In this case, you use Placeholder Settings. Placeholder Settings restrict which Sublayouts can be placed within a Placeholder. </p>
<h3>Activity</h3>
<p>In the Content Tree, under <strong>Sitecore &gt; Layout &gt; Placeholder Settings</strong>, you can create a new Placeholder Setting item for each Placeholder you wish to modify the allowed controls on. </p>
<p>Add a new Placeholder by right clicking and select <strong>Insert &gt; Placeholder</strong>. Name the Placeholder "myfirstsite content". </p>
<p>Click Edit on the <strong>Allowed Controls</strong> field and add "Generic Display" and "Content Display".</p>
<p><img alt="" width="600" src="~/media/283E671A39E94C738D7E6BECCFC21CF3.ashx" /></p>
<p>We have now restricted the sublayouts that can be added to the "myfirstsite content" placeholder on our Main Layout. </p>
